Here's a single self-contained HTML file that provides an interactive, step-through visualization for binary search. I've tried to address all your points:

*   **Sorted Array as Numbered Boxes:** The array elements are displayed as distinct, numbered boxes.
*   **Target Input Field:** You can enter the target number you're looking for.
*   **Step Button:** Clicking this button advances the search by one iteration.
*   **Highlighting Search Range and Mid:**
    *   The `low` and `high` pointers are clearly indicated with different colors.
    *   The `mid` element is highlighted in a distinct color during each step.
    *   Elements *outside* the current search range are visually deemphasized.
*   **Final Found or Not Found Result:** The result is displayed clearly at the end of the search.
*   **Self-Contained:** It's a single HTML file with all CSS and JavaScript embedded.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Interactive Binary Search Visualization</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f7f6;
            color: #333;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .controls {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            align-items: center;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .controls label {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #555;
        }

        .controls input[type="number"] {
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            width: 80px;
            font-size: 1em;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .controls button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: white;
            font-size: 1em;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
        }

        .controls button:hover {
            background-color: #2980b9;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }

        .controls button:disabled {
            background-color: #cccccc;
            cursor: not-allowed;
            transform: none;
        }

        #array-container {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 5px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            min-height: 100px; /* Ensure space even if array is small */
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
        }

        .array-box {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            background-color: #ecf0f1;
            border: 1px solid #bdc3c7;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #2c3e50;
            position: relative;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        }

        .array-box.out-of-range {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            border-color: #e0e6ea;
            color: #b0b0b0;
            opacity: 0.6;
        }

        .array-box.low-pointer::after,
        .array-box.high-pointer::after,
        .array-box.mid-pointer::after,
        .array-box.found::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            top: -15px;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            font-size: 0.7em;
            font-weight: normal;
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border-radius: 3px;
            white-space: nowrap;
            z-index: 10;
        }

        .array-box.low-pointer::after { content: 'Low'; background-color: #e67e22; }
        .array-box.high-pointer::after { content: 'High'; background-color: #e74c3c; }
        .array-box.mid-pointer::after { content: 'Mid'; background-color: #27ae60; }
        .array-box.found::after { content: 'Found!'; background-color: #28a745; top: -25px; }

        .array-box.mid-pointer {
            background-color: #2ecc71; /* Green for mid */
            border-color: #27ae60;
            color: white;
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }

        .array-box.low-pointer {
            background-color: #f39c12; /* Orange for low */
            border-color: #e67e22;
            color: white;
        }

        .array-box.high-pointer {
            background-color: #e74c3c; /* Red for high */
            border-color: #c0392b;
            color: white;
        }

        .array-box.found {
            background-color: #28a745; /* Darker green for found */
            border-color: #218838;
            color: white;
            transform: scale(1.1);
            box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(40, 167, 69, 0.6);
        }

        #result {
            margin-top: 30px;
            font-size: 1.3em;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #333;
            min-height: 2em; /* Reserve space */
            text-align: center;
        }

        .result-found {
            color: #28a745;
        }

        .result-not-found {
            color: #dc3545;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Interactive Binary Search</h1>

    <div class="controls">
        <label for="target-input">Target Value:</label>
        <input type="number" id="target-input" value="12">
        <button id="start-button">Start Search</button>
        <button id="step-button" disabled>Step</button>
        <button id="reset-button" disabled>Reset</button>
    </div>

    <div id="array-container">
        <!-- Array boxes will be rendered here by JavaScript -->
    </div>

    <div id="result">
        <!-- Search result will be displayed here -->
    </div>

    <script>
        const initialArray = [2, 5, 8, 12, 16, 23, 38, 56, 72, 91];
        let arr = [];
        let target = 0;
        let low = 0;
        let high = 0;
        let mid = 0;
        let foundIndex = -1;
        let searchStarted = false;
        let searchFinished = false;

        const arrayContainer = document.getElementById('array-container');
        const targetInput = document.getElementById('target-input');
        const startButton = document.getElementById('start-button');
        const stepButton = document.getElementById('step-button');
        const resetButton = document.getElementById('reset-button');
        const resultDiv = document.getElementById('result');

        function renderArray() {
            arrayContainer.innerHTML = '';
            arr.forEach((value, index) => {
                const box = document.createElement('div');
                box.classList.add('array-box');
                box.dataset.index = index;
                box.textContent = value;

                if (searchStarted && !searchFinished) {
                    if (index < low || index > high) {
                        box.classList.add('out-of-range');
                    }
                    if (index === low) {
                        box.classList.add('low-pointer');
                    }
                    if (index === high) {
                        box.classList.add('high-pointer');
                    }
                    if (index === mid) {
                        box.classList.add('mid-pointer');
                    }
                } else if (searchFinished && foundIndex !== -1 && index === foundIndex) {
                    box.classList.add('found');
                } else if (searchFinished && foundIndex === -1) {
                    // No specific styling for not found, elements stay default or out-of-range
                }

                arrayContainer.appendChild(box);
            });
        }

        function resetSearch() {
            arr = [...initialArray]; // Reset to original array
            target = parseInt(targetInput.value);
            low = 0;
            high = arr.length - 1;
            mid = 0;
            foundIndex = -1;
            searchStarted = false;
            searchFinished = false;
            resultDiv.textContent = '';
            targetInput.disabled = false;
            startButton.disabled = false;
            stepButton.disabled = true;
            resetButton.disabled = true;
            renderArray();
        }

        function startSearch() {
            target = parseInt(targetInput.value);
            if (isNaN(target)) {
                resultDiv.textContent = 'Please enter a valid number for target.';
                resultDiv.className = 'result-not-found';
                return;
            }

            resetSearch(); // Ensure clean state
            searchStarted = true;
            targetInput.disabled = true;
            startButton.disabled = true;
            stepButton.disabled = false;
            resetButton.disabled = false;
            resultDiv.textContent = 'Search started...';
            resultDiv.className = '';
            renderArray(); // Initial render with low/high
        }

        function stepSearch() {
            if (searchFinished) return;

            if (low <= high) {
                mid = Math.floor((low + high) / 2);
                renderArray(); // Render current state (low, high, mid) before comparison

                setTimeout(() => { // Small delay to highlight mid before moving
                    if (arr[mid] === target) {
                        foundIndex = mid;
                        searchFinished = true;
                        resultDiv.textContent = `Found ${target} at index ${mid}!`;
                        resultDiv.className = 'result-found';
                        stepButton.disabled = true;
                        renderArray(); // Final render with found element highlighted
                    } else if (arr[mid] < target) {
                        low = mid + 1;
                        resultDiv.textContent = `${arr[mid]} < ${target}. Adjusting low to ${low}.`;
                    } else { // arr[mid] > target
                        high = mid - 1;
                        resultDiv.textContent = `${arr[mid]} > ${target}. Adjusting high to ${high}.`;
                    }

                    if (low > high && foundIndex === -1) {
                        searchFinished = true;
                        resultDiv.textContent = `${target} not found in the array.`;
                        resultDiv.className = 'result-not-found';
                        stepButton.disabled = true;
                    }

                    if (!searchFinished) {
                        renderArray(); // Render array after low/high adjustment
                    }
                }, 700); // Adjust delay as needed for visualization
            } else {
                searchFinished = true;
                resultDiv.textContent = `${target} not found in the array.`;
                resultDiv.className = 'result-not-found';
                stepButton.disabled = true;
                renderArray(); // Final render to clear any lingering mid/low/high if not found
            }
        }

        // Event Listeners
        startButton.addEventListener('click', startSearch);
        stepButton.addEventListener('click', stepSearch);
        resetButton.addEventListener('click', resetSearch);
        targetInput.addEventListener('keypress', (e) => {
            if (e.key === 'Enter') {
                if (!searchStarted) {
                    startSearch();
                } else if (!searchFinished) {
                    stepSearch();
                }
            }
        });

        // Initialize on load
        resetSearch();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
